    "body": "Same issue here (originally submitted at https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib/issues/11393):\r\n\r\nI can reproduce the problem even without `%matplotlib inline` magic:\r\n\r\nSame cell:\r\n<img width=\"435\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-06-07 at 12 34 49\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44946/41110385-80ee9a1e-6a79-11e8-9862-93244e809a5d.png\">\r\n- Note that `plt.rcParams['figure.figsize']` returns `[6.0, 4.0]` instead of expected `[12.0, 6.0]`.\r\n- Note it did work for the line width\r\n- Same result if I switch the plt.rc calls\r\n\r\nDifferent cells:\r\n<img width=\"454\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-06-07 at 12 35 10\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44946/41110428-9e81a6c0-6a79-11e8-9a66-a0782216b534.png\">\r\nworks as expected\r\n\r\n### versions\r\n- Operating system: OS X Darwin 17.5.0 i386\r\n- Matplotlib version: 2.0.2\r\n- Matplotlib backend: module://ipykernel.pylab.backend_inline\r\n- Python version: 2.7.15.final.0 (anaconda distribution, default channels)\r\n- Jupyter version: Jupyter notebook 5.5.0, IPython 5.7.0\r\n\r\n"
